.DS_Store

# Logs
*.log
solara.log
web.log

# Pickle artifacts
*.pkl

# Raw GSS cumulative file (598 MB .dta + zip) — user-downloaded for the MHV S4
# constraint/B&G ingest. NEVER commit the raw data; the small derived series
# (data/mhv/gss_constraint_series.json) is the committed artifact.
data/gss_raw/

# Phase 8f investigation — variant-sweep diagnostic dumps (70+ JSONs).
# Keep the named result JSONs (phase8b_calibration_results.json,
# phase8d_historical_results.json, phase8e_*.json) — those are
# referenced from methods.md and the phase results docs.
phase8f_diag_*.json

# Phase 9 cluster-diversity investigation variant dumps + logs.
phase9_div_*.json
phase9_logs/

# Local research artifacts — kept on workstation, not in repo.
# Diagnostic dumps from sweep scripts land here.
local_artifacts/

# Phase 9 Tier-A sweep noise — keep blessed/baseline/sweep CSV,
# drop the per-boost intermediate JSONs that aren't referenced
# from phase9_results.md.
phase9_section11_boost_*.json
phase9_tier_a_score_boost_*.json
phase9_tier_a_descriptors_boost_*.csv
phase9_tier_a_sweep_log.txt
phase9_tier_a_blessed_log.txt
phase9_tier_c_sweep_log.txt
phase9_tier_c_blessed_log.txt

# Phase 9 empirical raw data — ANES CDF is 156 MB and the HTML
# codebook is 4 MB. Both are reproducible by re-downloading from
# https://electionstudies.org (urls in docs/specs/phase9_raw_data_sources.md).
# Keep the small methodology MDs and the codebook PDF; drop the bulk.
data/phase9_empirical/raw/timeseries_csv.csv
data/phase9_empirical/raw/codebook_html.html
data/phase9_empirical/raw/codebook_html_files/

# Phase 9 derived data — keep only `respondent_coordinates.csv` (the
# canonical recoded ANES output, ~1.25 MB) under version control.
# Everything else under data/phase9_empirical/ is regenerable:
#   - `.npy` pointclouds + KDEs: built by scripts/phase9_anes_target_builder.py
#   - derived/{coverage_table,party_centroids,polarization_series,
#     recode_log}.csv + acceptance_checks.txt + build_log.md +
#     {scaling,kde}_params.json + densities/: build diagnostics from
#     scripts/anes_2d_compass.py
#   - phase9_empirical_build_anes.json: build metadata from target_builder.
# After a fresh clone, run:
#   .venv/Scripts/python.exe scripts/phase9_anes_target_builder.py
# to regenerate the .npy fixtures the calibration loads.
data/phase9_empirical/*.npy
data/phase9_empirical/phase9_empirical_build_anes.json
data/phase9_empirical/derived/coverage_table.csv
data/phase9_empirical/derived/party_centroids.csv
data/phase9_empirical/derived/polarization_series.csv
data/phase9_empirical/derived/recode_log.csv
data/phase9_empirical/derived/acceptance_checks.txt
data/phase9_empirical/derived/build_log.md
data/phase9_empirical/derived/scaling_params.json
data/phase9_empirical/derived/kde_params.json
data/phase9_empirical/derived/densities/

# Editor / scratchpad detritus
*.tmp
*.bak
*.bak.py
*.py.tmp

# web_demo published data — 199 MB of regenerable per-tick trajectories
# (scripts/publish_web_data.py). The demo itself loads web_demo/cc-data.js
# (a small repacked bundle, committed). Regenerate with:
#   python scripts/publish_web_data.py && python scripts/repack_web_demo.py
/web/data/


# Internal investigation / planning notes — kept on workstation, not in
# the public repo (2026-06 decision). Holds the engine-knob-audit and MHV
# working docs (reviews, roadmap, mhv_spec, calibration interpretation) and
# the audit harness OUTPUTS (docs/internal/audit/*.json|md — regenerable by
# the committed scripts/audit/*.py instruments). Public docs may cite these
# as "internal audit notes"; the load-bearing conclusions are summarized in
# methods.md / ENGINE_KNOBS.md.
docs/internal/

